                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79682/34: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Walton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-23T15:00:00-00:44"
                            >December 23, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 23—12:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>133. Department’s 85, December 20, 6 p.m. President Barclay and I have already
                    discussed subject and Legislature will enact law enabling him to deal
                    effectively with situation along lines suggested by Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
